

Try and create these first > 

```bash
export $(dbus-launch)
```

to the .zshrc or .bashrc file 




and the addition of 

~/.config/systemd/

~/.config/systemd/user.conf >>> 
[Manager]
DefaultEnvironment="XDG_RUNTIME_DIR=/run/user/1000" "XAUTHORITY=/home/dwarf/.Xauthority" "DBUS_SESSION_BUS_ADDRESS=unix:path=/run/user/1000/bus"



then assess the state of the service itself and allow it to relink


systemctl --failed

## This will return a failure on the CLI
systemctl --user start user@1000.service


## This will generally show an error
systemctl status user@1000.service --all


systemctl status user@1000.service --all

> Produces output 


## ACTUALLY starts the service
sudo systemctl start user@1000.service


## Should be in an active state and "Ready" instead of broken.
systemctl status user@1000.service --all

